  "name": "RPlog_Work_Makes_for_Strange_Company_II",
  "title": "The Archaeologist and the Mandalorian",
  "summary": "Still ensconced in the hotel dining room days into his research, the smuggler-archaeologist Paul Nighman is approached by Grathix, a poised, reptilian-eyed being intrigued by Paul's muttered talk of artifacts and an ancient Corellian dialect. Over wine and coffee, Paul shows Grathix his prized find: an illuminated tome by a Corellian monk depicting the 'True Ones,' and a statue strikingly matching the manuscript's drawing. Grathix reveals himself as a vice president and foreign sales representative for MandalMotors, and the two discuss antiquities, archaeology, and Paul's misadventures with troublesome red-haired women, including the Imperial woman Luke Skywalker once followed. When the conversation turns to the Clone Wars and the lore of Jedi cloning artifacts, Grathix discloses that he is a Mandalorian and could tell Paul more than the ancient scribes, before excusing himself to keep an appointment with Luke Skywalker. He departs, leaving his muffin and tab behind, and Paul immediately sets his terminal searching for everything on Mandalore and its recovered artifacts.",
